WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:10.320 --> 01:12.004
(MUSIC PLAYING)

01:14.800 --> 01:17.406
Can I help you find something, sir?

01:19.440 --> 01:20.646
Um...

01:22.280 --> 01:24.726
Yeah, do you have any black napkins?

01:26.120 --> 01:28.009
I've been looking all over.

01:28.080 --> 01:30.845
Black napkins. I don't think so.

01:30.920 --> 01:32.365
If you don't like White,

01:32.440 --> 01:34.807
this is a beige one.

01:36.800 --> 01:38.211
They have to be black.

01:39.000 --> 01:41.241
That's more of a Halloween item.

01:41.320 --> 01:43.402
You might want to try a party store.

01:58.680 --> 01:59.681
Hi.

01:59.920 --> 02:00.921
Um...

02:01.000 --> 02:02.684
You guys ran out last night so...

02:02.760 --> 02:04.762
Oh, that was so thoughtful of you.

02:04.840 --> 02:07.241
Thank you. Thank you. Come on in.

02:07.320 --> 02:10.244
- Maury, how are you holding up?
- Hi. Uh...

02:10.320 --> 02:11.446
- You know.
- Yeah.

02:11.520 --> 02:13.807
Noah, come on in. Come on in.

02:15.600 --> 02:17.489
WOMAN: I just don't know what I would do.

02:17.880 --> 02:20.929
I keep thinking about her sweet little face
in Mommy and Me.

02:21.000 --> 02:23.367
Just the most perfect little girl.

02:23.440 --> 02:26.523
- Beth... Just so dear.
- WOMAN: No, of course not.

02:28.200 --> 02:30.328
- MAN: Is that turkey?
- It's turkey pastrami.

02:30.400 --> 02:32.209
- Pastrami turkey?
- Yeah.

02:32.280 --> 02:33.930
The pink one is turkey pastrami.

02:41.200 --> 02:44.204
WOMAN: Just the most
lovely baby of them all.

02:44.280 --> 02:46.408
What a dear child.

02:46.520 --> 02:47.646
It's hard to understand.

02:47.720 --> 02:50.564
Zach, I'm so sorry.

02:51.080 --> 02:52.127
Um...

02:52.200 --> 02:54.009
Thank you, Mr. Levin.

02:54.560 --> 02:56.403
She was a special girl.

03:05.880 --> 03:07.723
JUDY: Kyle, we're back.

03:07.800 --> 03:09.564
- I'm gonna take a nap.
- NOAH: Okay.

03:09.640 --> 03:11.165
Hey. you okay?

03:11.240 --> 03:12.605
Yeah, I'm fine.

03:12.680 --> 03:14.170
How did it go?

03:15.080 --> 03:16.411
What kind of a question is that?

03:16.480 --> 03:17.481
Zachy.

03:17.720 --> 03:20.883
I mean, is that really the problem?
Is it the garden or is it you guys?

03:24.000 --> 03:25.525
(TALKING INDISTINCTLY)

03:35.600 --> 03:37.523
NOAH: Well, it's not just beaches there.
They have...

03:37.600 --> 03:40.763
- it's islands. Two islands?
- There's mostly... Well, the Turks.

03:40.840 --> 03:42.080
- And then, there's the Caicos.
- The Caicos.

03:42.200 --> 03:44.202
We don't have to go to both.
We can just go to Turks.

03:44.280 --> 03:45.645
You know what?
We don't have to decide tonight,

03:45.720 --> 03:47.245
- but you'll think about it.
- JUDY: You'll think about it.

03:47.320 --> 03:50.051
NOAH: We know it's been a tough time.
But Turks and Caicos?

03:50.120 --> 03:55.286
<i>KYLE: I talked to Sam Hirsch today,
and he said, "The reason I've been..."</i>

03:55.960 --> 03:57.883
(CAR LOCK BEEPS)

04:12.320 --> 04:14.891
PEARLINE: I'm getting out of here.
MAURY: Pearline, where are you going?

04:14.960 --> 04:16.769
- Geenie gave you the day off.
- Don't go in there, Zachery.

04:16.839 --> 04:18.046
Pearline!

04:18.640 --> 04:20.165
- I'm never coming back.
- Can we please talk?

04:20.279 --> 04:21.725
PEARLINE: I've had enough, you see.

04:21.800 --> 04:24.724
- Enough. No more...
- If this is a bad time, then I think...

04:24.800 --> 04:25.880
Zach, can you believe this?

04:28.320 --> 04:30.402
You want to come inside?

04:30.640 --> 04:32.051
Yikes!

04:32.880 --> 04:34.245
I just don't understand, you know.

04:34.320 --> 04:35.845
- We gave her the day off.
- MAURY: Right?

04:35.960 --> 04:37.200
Now, of all times.

04:37.280 --> 04:39.567
- It's just not like her.
- She's lost her mind clearly.

04:39.640 --> 04:41.961
- GEENIE: She can't leave us, not now.
- (STUTTERS)

04:42.040 --> 04:43.320
She needs a break. I don't know.

04:43.360 --> 04:45.931
Um, what are you doing here?

04:46.000 --> 04:48.810
I'm just organizing Beth's stuff, you know.

04:50.160 --> 04:52.970
- Her stuffed animals and...
- ZACH: Oh, wow.

04:57.280 --> 04:58.930
GEENIE: Pictures.

04:59.000 --> 05:01.731
I really didn't take enough pictures.

05:01.800 --> 05:03.609
So foolish.

05:03.680 --> 05:05.011
Eating Jell-O.

05:05.440 --> 05:08.762
Oh, we used to eat Jell-O all the time
when Beth was little.

05:09.520 --> 05:11.124
We ate a lot of Jell-O.

05:11.200 --> 05:12.770
Yeah, we did.

05:19.000 --> 05:21.321
I can't even focus anymore.

05:22.200 --> 05:24.202
I'm a mess, Mr. Slocum.

05:25.640 --> 05:27.722
You can call me Maury.

05:28.960 --> 05:30.405
Okay.

05:30.880 --> 05:31.961
(CHUCKLES)

05:32.040 --> 05:33.371
Maury-

05:35.240 --> 05:39.245
I think I have something
that might help us both.

05:39.960 --> 05:44.727
Geenie's been keeping really busy
with all this cleaning.

05:46.480 --> 05:48.960
(SIGHS) It's therapeutic, I guess.

05:49.040 --> 05:51.327
And you still have your band, right?

05:51.400 --> 05:54.563
Oh, we broke up. I mean, I left them.

05:54.880 --> 05:56.291
Ah.

05:56.760 --> 05:59.161
You know, I'll never play music again.

06:03.480 --> 06:04.481
(SIGHS)

06:05.400 --> 06:06.481
(INHALES)

06:17.160 --> 06:18.446
(STAMMERING) Oh, I'm okay.

06:18.520 --> 06:19.760
Come on.

06:20.440 --> 06:22.363
- Well, I don't...
- Take it.

06:22.440 --> 06:24.568
You're calling me Maury.

06:25.400 --> 06:26.811
(CHUCKLES)

06:36.680 --> 06:40.127
- Can I tell you something, Maury?
- Sure.

06:41.720 --> 06:46.886
Beth and I were having troubles
before she...

06:46.960 --> 06:48.530
I know.

06:48.920 --> 06:50.445
She told me.

06:52.040 --> 06:54.964
- Really?
- Look, the last time I spoke to her,

06:55.040 --> 06:58.044
I was telling her
she had to go to the dentist,

06:58.120 --> 07:00.726
and she told I was being annoying.

07:00.800 --> 07:03.804
That's the last thing she said to me.
"Dad, you're being annoying."

07:04.640 --> 07:08.122
Now, I could choose to remember that
for the rest of my life

07:08.240 --> 07:11.050
as being emblematic
of my connection with my daughter.

07:11.120 --> 07:14.044
Yeah, but then it's all arbitrary then,
you know.

07:14.160 --> 07:17.164
Because, like, we only remember
the moments that we want to and...

07:17.240 --> 07:21.040
You can't let that last moment
define the entire relationship.

07:21.120 --> 07:22.690
- It'll drive you crazy.
- I know. I know.

07:22.760 --> 07:26.287
But there's just, like, so many things
that I wish I had told her

07:26.360 --> 07:29.204
that I just, like, never even...

07:29.280 --> 07:31.044
I never said to her.

07:31.960 --> 07:33.485
Me, too.

07:33.760 --> 07:35.091
(INHALES)

07:38.960 --> 07:40.325
I love you, Zach.

07:41.560 --> 07:43.562
I love you, too.

07:47.080 --> 07:48.081
Oh.

07:48.160 --> 07:49.161
Bye.

07:56.680 --> 07:59.047
Aspen with the Goldfarbs.

07:59.720 --> 08:00.846
Can I have that?

08:01.520 --> 08:02.851
Sure.

08:08.080 --> 08:10.321
- It's summer though.
- Oh, I don't care.

08:10.520 --> 08:12.807
- (CHUCKLES)
- it's hers.

08:28.880 --> 08:30.564
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

08:54.240 --> 08:56.846
JUDY: Zach?
NOAH: Jesus Christ, Judy.

08:56.920 --> 08:58.001
JUDY: Where were you?
NOAH: Stop yelling.

08:58.080 --> 09:00.367
I was playing chess at the Slocums'.

09:00.440 --> 09:02.568
JUDY: It's 3:00 in the morning!

09:02.640 --> 09:03.687
I know.

09:03.760 --> 09:04.921
JUDY: What?

09:05.000 --> 09:06.126
Okay!

09:09.200 --> 09:10.804
JUDY: Zach, are you coming to bed?

09:10.880 --> 09:12.564
- Yes!
- NOAH: Just go to sleep.

09:25.440 --> 09:27.010
(DOORBELL RINGS)

09:29.760 --> 09:30.761
(ANSWERING MACHINE BEEPS)

09:30.960 --> 09:34.169
ZACH: <i>Hey,</i> Maury <i>and Mrs. Slocum,
or Geenie.</i>

09:34.240 --> 09:36.163
<i>Guess I can call you Geenie.</i>

09:36.240 --> 09:38.766
<i>Stopped by today with Jell-O,</i>

09:38.840 --> 09:42.049
and I just, uh...

09:42.760 --> 09:46.731
I don't know. You can call me back, like,
whenever you can, okay?

09:46.800 --> 09:49.849
Um, bye, love you.

09:49.920 --> 09:50.967
(PHONE BEEPS)

09:51.040 --> 09:52.041
NOAH: Let me tell you something.

09:52.120 --> 09:55.044
I tried a provolone cheese today
from Canada. So tart.

09:55.120 --> 09:56.884
You're not eating tonight, Zach?

09:57.320 --> 09:58.970
- I'm not hungry.
- Pfft.

09:59.880 --> 10:01.006
NOAH: You should eat something.

10:01.120 --> 10:02.167
Come on, son, eat.

10:02.240 --> 10:05.767
Did anyone leave a message for me today?
The Slocums?

10:05.840 --> 10:07.126
Nope. Not today.

10:07.200 --> 10:08.725
I think they're avoiding me.

10:08.800 --> 10:11.849
You're, uh, spending a lot of time
with Maury Slocum, huh?

10:11.920 --> 10:12.921
JUDY: Well, are they all right?

10:13.000 --> 10:15.571
I don't know.
We never even finished the chess game.

10:15.640 --> 10:17.210
The one till 3:00 in the morning,
you didn't finish?

10:17.280 --> 10:18.566
- Now I'm worried.
- NOAH: You know what?

10:18.680 --> 10:20.205
- I hope they're all right.
- KYLE: What did you do to them?

10:20.280 --> 10:21.930
JUDY: You played till 3:00,
and you still didn't finish?

10:22.000 --> 10:24.401
- It was a really good game.
- What did you do with them?

10:24.760 --> 10:26.569
Nothing, Kyle.

10:26.640 --> 10:28.244
I'm so sure of that. Yeah.

10:28.320 --> 10:30.800
Why are you wearing a scarf? It's summer.

10:30.880 --> 10:32.370
It's Beth's.

10:33.680 --> 10:34.647
(STAMMERING) Where you going?

10:34.720 --> 10:36.210
- You haven't eaten anything.
- ZACH: I'm tired.

10:36.320 --> 10:38.800
Well, I think we should see a neurologist.
You're acting very strange.

10:38.880 --> 10:40.450
- No, I'm not acting strange.
- Definitely acting strange.

10:40.520 --> 10:42.170
- Acting suspicious.
- I'm tired.

10:42.240 --> 10:45.050
- So, where... You're going to sleep now?
- Yes.

10:45.320 --> 10:46.321
(SCOFFS)

10:48.520 --> 10:50.727
- You'll never guess who called today.
- (DOOR CLOSES)

10:51.920 --> 10:53.604
Sharon Wexler.

11:18.520 --> 11:20.363
- (SCREAMS) Jesus, Kyle!
- KYLE: What the fuck are you doing?

11:20.440 --> 11:21.965
- Are you fucking your scarf?
- No.

11:22.040 --> 11:23.485
Yeah, you are. You're fucking your scarf.

11:23.560 --> 11:26.131
It's my dead girlfriend's scarf, okay?
She's dead.

11:26.200 --> 11:29.249
- Do you know what that's like? I was just...
- (DOOR CLOSES)

11:30.560 --> 11:31.925
(SIGHS)

11:41.200 --> 11:43.009
(TV PLAYING INDISTINCTLY)

11:57.760 --> 11:59.410
(DOORBELL RINGS)

12:02.040 --> 12:03.530
(TV TURNS OFF)

12:12.360 --> 12:13.771
(DOORBELL RINGING)

12:33.760 --> 12:35.091
(DOOR CREAKS)

13:05.560 --> 13:07.050
(INAUDIBLE)

13:08.640 --> 13:10.005
Beth?

13:11.000 --> 13:13.082
- Beth! Beth!
- (DOG BARKING)

13:13.160 --> 13:14.400
Maury-

13:14.520 --> 13:17.000
Maury, go to the door. Beth!

13:17.800 --> 13:20.770
Geenie!

13:20.840 --> 13:23.081
Beth!

13:23.160 --> 13:25.811
Beth, it's me. It's Zach. It's me.

13:25.880 --> 13:29.248
- Geenie! Maury, Maury!
- (CAR PULLING OVER)

13:29.320 --> 13:30.765
Come on, you guys.

13:30.840 --> 13:33.320
Open the door. I know she's in there.

13:33.400 --> 13:35.129
What do you think you're doing?

13:35.200 --> 13:37.441
Kyle. Kyle, I just saw... (PANTING)

13:37.520 --> 13:40.285
I saw Beth. Beth is inside.

13:40.360 --> 13:41.691
You're fucking crazy.

13:41.760 --> 13:43.444
And now you're harassing
the residents of Briar Grove.

13:43.520 --> 13:45.727
- What? No, I'm not. Come on. Give a break.
- No, you give me a break.

13:45.800 --> 13:46.926
- You step away from that door.
- What? No.

13:47.000 --> 13:48.968
Step... Zach...

13:49.040 --> 13:50.041
- I'll fucking mace you.
- Okay.

13:50.120 --> 13:51.645
- I don't want to do it, but I'll mace you.
- Okay.

13:51.720 --> 13:53.927
All right, stand right there.

13:54.000 --> 13:55.525
- Around.
- Fine.

13:57.480 --> 13:58.811
(KYLE SIGHS)

13:58.880 --> 14:00.450
Had to make a scene, huh?

14:03.440 --> 14:04.726
(DOORBELL RINGS)

14:04.880 --> 14:05.881
(KYLE SIGHS)

14:07.760 --> 14:09.410
Mr. and Mrs. Slocum, it's the BGS.

14:09.480 --> 14:12.165
- She is in there. I saw her.
- Shut up. Shut up.

14:13.440 --> 14:15.442
- Shut up. Shut up.
- I didn't even say anything.

14:15.520 --> 14:17.170
I know.
I could feel you about to say something.

14:17.240 --> 14:19.040
MAURY: Everything's fine now, Kyle.
Thank you.

14:19.080 --> 14:20.491
- What? Maury, Maury.
- Shut up! Shut up!

14:20.560 --> 14:22.050
- Thank you, Mr. Slocum.
- Maury, what is going on?

14:22.120 --> 14:24.881
- I want you to have a great day. Thank you.
- I saw Beth. I saw Beth.

14:24.920 --> 14:26.206
- What are you doing?
- You need to relax.

14:26.280 --> 14:28.328
You need to shut up.
You need to get a hold of yourself.

14:28.400 --> 14:32.086
You need to get in your fucking Saab, and
put it in reverse, and drive out of here.

14:32.160 --> 14:35.004
Look, please. Okay, please. She's in there.

14:35.080 --> 14:38.687
Okay, will you just search the house?
Will you just ask to search the house?

14:38.760 --> 14:41.809
She's not in there, and I can't do that.

14:41.880 --> 14:43.484
Well, great. Well, what can you do?

14:43.560 --> 14:45.528
I can ask escort you
to the perimeter of the premises.

14:45.600 --> 14:48.490
And if you resist, I can call the police.
That's what I can do.

14:48.560 --> 14:50.210
- Just get the fuck out of here.
- Come on, Kyle.

14:50.280 --> 14:51.725
Get the fuck out of here.

14:51.800 --> 14:53.848
- This is ridiculous.
- Get the fuck out of here.

14:53.920 --> 14:55.365
Come on.

14:55.440 --> 14:56.441
(SIGHS)

14:56.880 --> 14:59.087
(MUSIC PLAYING)

15:52.400 --> 15:55.404
MAURY: This is good for Beth.

16:00.000 --> 16:02.128
- Who's there?
- It's Zach.

16:02.680 --> 16:03.920
MAURY: Zach, go away!

16:04.000 --> 16:05.126
ZACH: Fuck.

16:06.960 --> 16:08.086
<i>MAURY: Zach.</i>

16:08.160 --> 16:09.685
Zach, you need to go.

16:09.760 --> 16:11.285
- Where is she?
- Who?

16:11.360 --> 16:13.442
- Beth.
- Listen, (SCOFFS)

16:14.080 --> 16:16.606
if you're upset at me
for not returning your call...

16:16.680 --> 16:18.091
No, she is not dead. Is she?

16:18.160 --> 16:19.605
That's why you've been so secretive
about everything.

16:19.680 --> 16:20.806
- Zach, listen...
- Am I right?

16:20.880 --> 16:23.360
- Am I right, Maury? Just tell me.
- You're not right.

16:23.440 --> 16:24.566
- You're upset.
- Beth.

16:24.640 --> 16:27.564
- Listen, Zach, you need to leave.
- Beth! Beth!

16:28.680 --> 16:30.364
MAURY: Zach!
ZACH: Beth!

16:30.440 --> 16:32.408
MAURY: Geenie? Geenie!

16:32.480 --> 16:33.925
- Beth! Beth!
- GEENIE: Quick, honey, get in the closet.

16:34.000 --> 16:35.889
- MAURY: Geenie! Geenie!
- Beth!

16:35.960 --> 16:38.691
- GEENIE: Hide in the closet! Close...
- Mom.

16:39.240 --> 16:42.369
- Okay. Okay.
- Oh, my gosh! Oh, my gosh, Maury.

16:42.480 --> 16:44.130
Look who I found. It's Beth.

16:44.200 --> 16:45.840
- All right, calm down, Zach.
- It's Beth!

16:45.880 --> 16:47.644
What you doing? Hey, I have that scarf.

16:47.720 --> 16:49.051
What was I supposed to do?
He ran around me.

16:49.120 --> 16:50.929
- He made a juke, and he ran around me.
- Stop him in the hall!

16:51.000 --> 16:52.650
What is going on here?
What is going on here?

16:52.720 --> 16:54.722
You're acting like a spaz.

16:54.800 --> 16:55.961
- It's a little bit hard to explain.
- GEENIE: Yes.

16:56.040 --> 16:57.201
How could you do this to me, Beth?

16:57.280 --> 16:59.408
- You made me think that you were...
- MAURY: Hey, hey, hey, hey, Zach.

16:59.480 --> 17:02.165
- She didn't do anything.
- Everything's normal. This just happened.

17:02.240 --> 17:04.641
- What just happened? What did I do?
- Nothing happened. It's normal.

17:04.720 --> 17:06.210
- You're fine.
- Everything is completely normal.

17:06.280 --> 17:07.486
- Just tell me. Just tell me.
- You're totally fine.

17:07.560 --> 17:09.324
- Tell me why you shut me out.
- Tell you what?

17:09.400 --> 17:12.801
Zach, why don't you and I go out
and have a little conversation in private?

17:12.880 --> 17:16.009
- No, Maury, no. You lied to me.
- I think that's a wonderful idea.

17:16.079 --> 17:17.127
- I never lied.
- BETH: What are you talking about?

17:17.200 --> 17:18.440
- Why are you acting all weird?
- Calm down.

17:18.520 --> 17:20.647
I'm not acting weird.
Stop playing dumb, Beth.

17:20.720 --> 17:23.564
- I'm not playing dumb. You're freaking out.
- That is no way talk to my daughter.

17:23.640 --> 17:27.166
- You know what? Fuck you people.
- Listen to me, Zach. You need to calm down.

17:27.240 --> 17:28.765
Look, this is good. This is a good thing.

17:28.840 --> 17:31.127
How could you people?
A fucking snakebite?

17:31.200 --> 17:33.009
Please stop. You're scaring me.
You're acting all crazy.

17:33.080 --> 17:34.241
This is all happening very fast.

17:34.320 --> 17:35.685
- No, I am not acting crazy.
- And you're confused.

17:35.760 --> 17:36.841
- You're all crazy.
- MAURY: You're confused.

17:36.920 --> 17:38.251
ZACH: Do you have any idea
what you put me through?

17:38.320 --> 17:39.731
- It's okay.
- All of you.

17:39.800 --> 17:41.484
You know what? You know what, Beth?

17:41.560 --> 17:45.121
It is one thing to say that
you want to see other people, okay?

17:45.200 --> 17:46.884
- What?
- I am a wreck.

17:47.000 --> 17:50.049
Don't say anything
you wouldn't want to say now like...

17:50.120 --> 17:51.884
You were supposed to be my friend.

17:51.960 --> 17:53.166
- I still am. We are friends.
- Wait a minute.

17:53.240 --> 17:56.210
- Who said I wanted to break up with you?
- Let's talk. You're upset. Let's talk.

17:56.280 --> 17:58.487
- Did Rachel say that to you?
- MAURY: We're all upset now...

17:58.560 --> 18:00.483
- Did she call you?
- MAURY: Listen, Zach.

18:01.880 --> 18:02.881
(DOOR SHUTTING)

18:04.360 --> 18:06.283
Hey, look who's here.

18:06.360 --> 18:07.805
Zach, is everything all right?

18:07.880 --> 18:10.565
Oh, yeah, everything's great. Beth's alive.
It was all just one big hoax.

18:10.640 --> 18:12.483
So just forget about it.

18:12.800 --> 18:14.131
Well, I don't think that's funny.

18:14.200 --> 18:17.090
Yeah, well, I don't either.

18:18.680 --> 18:19.806
(DOOR SHUTTING)

18:20.040 --> 18:21.405
(MACHINE WHIRRING)

19:14.880 --> 19:16.928
Come on. Hurry, hurry.

19:22.760 --> 19:24.603
ZACH: I went to her grave.

19:25.080 --> 19:27.048
There's a hole in the ground.

19:29.280 --> 19:30.850
Well... (SIGHS)

19:33.000 --> 19:34.729
She's not dead, Zach.

19:36.040 --> 19:38.407
Look, what kind of a grift is this?

19:38.800 --> 19:40.245
This is not a grift.

19:40.840 --> 19:43.764
Okay, okay.
Well, then why couldn't you tell me?

19:44.040 --> 19:46.725
Because she died.

19:47.800 --> 19:49.131
- What?
- She died.

19:49.200 --> 19:51.282
She died, and she's not dead now.

19:51.360 --> 19:55.365
I don't know why. But she's back.
Who cares why?

19:55.440 --> 19:56.885
My daughter's alive, Zach.

19:56.960 --> 20:00.123
Look, I am not stupid, okay?

20:00.200 --> 20:02.328
And I will go to the police.

20:02.400 --> 20:04.562
Tell me what happened.

20:04.680 --> 20:07.763
The doorbell rang
about a half an hour after you left

20:07.840 --> 20:09.251
the night we played chess,

20:09.320 --> 20:10.446
and it was Beth.

20:11.600 --> 20:13.523
We don't know how, okay?

20:13.600 --> 20:15.443
Okay. Okay, great.

20:15.520 --> 20:17.522
So this is not a grift, right?

20:17.600 --> 20:20.206
So then what is it?
Because you said she was really dead.

20:20.320 --> 20:22.402
And then you said she wasn't dead.
So, what are you saying?

20:22.480 --> 20:26.166
Are you saying that
she just dug herself out of her own grave

20:26.240 --> 20:28.971
- and then walked home?
- Yes.

20:29.080 --> 20:30.605
I don't know.

20:30.880 --> 20:31.881
She... Uh...

20:32.280 --> 20:33.964
Was it the type of snake?

20:34.040 --> 20:37.169
Was it a poison that didn't...
That made her seem dead?

20:37.240 --> 20:40.210
I'm not a herpetologist, Zach. I
don't know. She remembers nothing.

20:40.280 --> 20:42.886
I mean, what is that?
She's dead, now she's not dead.

20:42.960 --> 20:44.530
- What, she like...
- Crazy things happen.

20:44.600 --> 20:45.761
ZACH: She wasn't really dead?

20:45.840 --> 20:48.366
What is that? What are you saying?
Are you saying that she's a zombie?

20:48.440 --> 20:50.488
- She's my baby girl.
- Don't look a gift horse in the mouth.

20:50.600 --> 20:52.045
- It's a miracle.
- It's a miracle.

20:52.120 --> 20:53.724
- She's resurrected.
- She's resurrected.

20:53.800 --> 20:55.325
She could be a zombie!

20:55.440 --> 20:56.965
Stop saying that, please.
It's a resurrection.

20:57.040 --> 20:58.485
- Resurrection!
- She's resurrected!

20:58.560 --> 21:01.040
Okay, and that's better why? Why is
that better? Because that's a nice...

21:01.120 --> 21:02.240
It's from the Old Testament.

21:02.320 --> 21:06.769
Shouldn't we call someone at Harvard
or MIT and have them study her?

21:06.840 --> 21:09.446
- Keep your voice down. She's upstairs.
- BETH: Mom, have you seen my jewelry?

21:09.520 --> 21:10.601
What is going on?

21:10.680 --> 21:14.048
Sweetheart, it's in the Bankers Box
with your sticker collection.

21:14.120 --> 21:15.440
Why is all my stuff in boxes now?

21:15.480 --> 21:16.561
Not a word, Zach.

21:16.640 --> 21:17.766
BETH: Hey, Zach.

21:17.880 --> 21:19.245
Hey, Beth.

21:20.880 --> 21:23.406
- Do you want to go hang out in the attic?
- The attic? No. Why the attic?

21:23.480 --> 21:25.767
- She likes the attic.
- Why? What's with all this why?

21:25.840 --> 21:27.251
- Why? Why?
- Can't we just do something else?

21:27.320 --> 21:30.051
MAURY: Why not enjoy yourself?
GEENIE: Wait, smile!

21:30.120 --> 21:32.043
Oh, I love it!

21:32.120 --> 21:33.963
Go, Zach. Just go.

21:34.040 --> 21:37.010
Go and tell her what you wanted to tell her
when you couldn't.

21:37.960 --> 21:40.361
- Come on. It'll be fun.
- No. Hold on a sec.

21:42.200 --> 21:45.090
You go first. I'm right behind you.

21:53.200 --> 21:54.690
Come here.

22:02.720 --> 22:04.529
Your hair is so warm.

22:05.880 --> 22:07.803
My hair is warm?

22:07.880 --> 22:09.803
What... What does that mean?

22:09.880 --> 22:12.167
Zach, why are you acting so weird?

22:13.360 --> 22:16.045
Like what's going on
with you and Mom and Dad?

22:16.120 --> 22:17.804
Everyone's so weird.

22:19.200 --> 22:23.000
Do you really not remember
what happened last week?

22:24.040 --> 22:28.250
I'm sorry. Did I do something
that pissed you off or something?

22:29.760 --> 22:31.330
Just tell me what you remember.

22:32.440 --> 22:34.522
(SIGHS) I don't know. It's a blur. Why?

22:34.600 --> 22:38.161
What about going hiking alone?

22:38.720 --> 22:42.247
(SIGHS) Honestly, I can't really
think straight right now.

22:43.440 --> 22:45.329
I'm pretty nervous about my test tomorrow.

22:45.400 --> 22:48.051
- What test? It's the summer.
- (SCOFFS)

22:48.520 --> 22:49.885
I Wish.

22:52.600 --> 22:54.728
What about breaking up with me?

22:54.800 --> 22:56.689
And what about...

22:56.760 --> 22:58.922
Why do you keep saying that?

23:00.200 --> 23:02.771
I don't want to break up with you, Zach.

23:02.840 --> 23:04.251
I love you.

23:04.880 --> 23:08.680
I would never want to break up with you.
I don't know why you keep saying...

23:08.760 --> 23:11.923
Hey. Beth, sweetie.

23:12.000 --> 23:13.001
Hey, don't cry.

23:13.120 --> 23:15.202
- Why are you being so mean?
- I'm not being mean.

23:15.280 --> 23:16.441
- I just...
- Yes, you are.

23:16.520 --> 23:18.124
No, I...

23:18.200 --> 23:19.804
Look, I've just...

23:19.880 --> 23:22.770
I've just been having
a lot of thoughts about us recently.

23:23.520 --> 23:26.251
- Like bad stuff?
- Um... No. No, no, no, no.

23:26.320 --> 23:27.810
Like really good stuff.

23:27.880 --> 23:34.126
Like, you are my favorite person
in the whole world.

23:34.640 --> 23:35.641
(CHUCKLES)

23:36.280 --> 23:40.490
And I wish we went hiking together more.

23:41.480 --> 23:45.565
And, like, I wish that I went
flamenco dancing with you

23:45.640 --> 23:48.769
every time you asked.

23:48.840 --> 23:50.330
And, um...

23:51.880 --> 23:55.282
And whenever you go away,

23:55.360 --> 23:57.931
you're the only thing I can think of.

23:58.640 --> 24:02.531
I think of you all the time too.
All the time.

24:02.600 --> 24:06.286
I'm so happy that you're back.

24:06.360 --> 24:08.089
And I just... I don't...

24:08.160 --> 24:12.051
I really want it to last this time.
(PANTING)

24:12.120 --> 24:13.724
Zach, I love you so much.

24:13.800 --> 24:16.326
I fucking love you so goddamn much.

24:21.840 --> 24:22.887
Wait.

24:22.960 --> 24:24.564
- What?
- Wait, not...

24:24.640 --> 24:26.881
Not with my parents downstairs.

24:27.800 --> 24:31.407
Okay, do you want to go somewhere?
Like, hiking?

24:31.480 --> 24:33.084
- Yeah.
- Okay.

24:33.760 --> 24:35.524
Okay, let's go.

24:42.120 --> 24:43.121
(CAMERA BEEPING)

24:43.200 --> 24:44.929
GEENIE: You two have fun?
ZACH: Oh, yeah.

24:45.000 --> 24:46.809
We're gonna go for a hike.

24:46.920 --> 24:48.331
- Ooh.
- Not a hot idea.

24:48.400 --> 24:49.520
Oh. Whoa! In broad daylight?

24:49.920 --> 24:50.921
Zach, are you nuts?

24:51.000 --> 24:53.048
- Wait till nightfall.
- Why?

24:53.120 --> 24:55.771
- Because, baby, it's safer.
- At night?

24:55.840 --> 24:57.490
- Who hikes at night?
- Nobody hikes at night.

24:57.600 --> 25:00.410
We can watch TV till nightfall.

25:00.480 --> 25:01.891
Zach.

25:04.040 --> 25:06.611
Oh, yeah, okay.
Okay, yeah, that sounds good.

25:07.120 --> 25:08.121
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

25:08.200 --> 25:10.851
- I'll get it.
- BOTH: No! No, no, no!

25:10.920 --> 25:13.605
- Guys?
- It's fine. I'll get it.

25:13.680 --> 25:15.364
- Daddy gets it.
- You hate getting the phone!

25:15.440 --> 25:16.885
MAURY: I know, but I like it now.

25:17.920 --> 25:20.764
<i>NARRATOR: (ON TV) Pachacuti,
the powerful lncan Emperor,</i>

25:20.840 --> 25:23.241
<i>who ordered the construction
of Machu Picchu...</i>

25:23.320 --> 25:25.322
Why don't you two
just hang out here tonight?

25:25.720 --> 25:28.644
Beth has a test tomorrow.
It's already late so...

25:28.720 --> 25:30.449
Yeah, but you said that we could...

25:30.520 --> 25:31.965
<i>We could play Scrabble.</i>

25:32.040 --> 25:34.088
Like why don't we just go for a drive
or something?

25:34.160 --> 25:35.764
You know, something private?

25:36.320 --> 25:38.527
(WHISPERING) Discretion, Zach. Discretion.

25:38.640 --> 25:40.404
- We could go swimming.
- GEENIE: Ooh!

25:40.760 --> 25:43.286
That's a good idea. So romantic.

25:43.360 --> 25:45.328
The pool's heated. I don't see why not.

25:45.400 --> 25:46.890
Go swimming.

25:46.960 --> 25:49.486
I don't have a bathing suit so...

25:49.560 --> 25:51.688
- You can borrow one of mine.
- Yeah.

25:51.760 --> 25:55.924
Well, I don't want to impose,
so maybe we could just go for a drive.

25:56.000 --> 25:58.002
- You're not imposing.
- It's just a bathing suit.

25:58.080 --> 25:59.760
NARRATOR: <i>(ON TV)... empire into darkness.</i>

26:02.640 --> 26:04.130
ZACH: Are these awesome, or what?

26:14.280 --> 26:15.611
Is something wrong?

26:15.680 --> 26:17.569
I'm just really nervous
for that test tomorrow.

26:17.680 --> 26:18.681
What test?

26:19.800 --> 26:20.801
Oh.

26:22.240 --> 26:23.605
Oh, yeah.

26:24.840 --> 26:26.251
Me, too.

26:33.800 --> 26:35.165
(CAMERA BEEPING)

26:35.560 --> 26:36.561
(ZACH SCOFFS)

26:38.320 --> 26:41.244
Your mom sure is taking a lot of pictures.

26:49.480 --> 26:51.005
You don't want to eat me, do you?

26:51.080 --> 26:52.650
Zach.

26:52.720 --> 26:55.246
Not right now, remember?

26:55.320 --> 26:56.845
No, I mean really eat me.

26:56.920 --> 27:01.084
Stop. Not with my parents around. Come on.

27:05.240 --> 27:07.527
That's so weird.
What was I just talking about?

27:09.920 --> 27:11.160
Nothing.

27:20.040 --> 27:21.451
You're so beautiful.

27:23.840 --> 27:26.525
I can't believe you're here.

27:27.360 --> 27:29.249
Where else would I be?

27:41.720 --> 27:45.008
- I had a really good time tonight.
- Me, too.

27:48.280 --> 27:49.805
- Good night.
- Good night.

27:59.880 --> 28:01.450
I love you.

28:02.960 --> 28:04.689
No, I love you more.

28:04.760 --> 28:06.649
Yes, I do.

28:06.720 --> 28:07.881
(LAUGHING) No.

28:10.480 --> 28:12.562
I want to eat your face off.

28:17.400 --> 28:19.846
- Hey, man, what are you doing?
- Nothing.

28:19.920 --> 28:22.002
I'm just cleaning Desert Eagle. Why?
It's not like you care.

28:22.080 --> 28:23.081
I care.

28:23.160 --> 28:24.400
Yeah, right.

28:24.480 --> 28:26.244
Hey-

28:26.320 --> 28:27.651
Look, um...

28:28.600 --> 28:30.090
I'm really sorry about the other day.

28:30.160 --> 28:32.083
Okay, I know you were just doing your job,

28:32.160 --> 28:35.209
and I know that I can sound
condescending sometimes,

28:35.280 --> 28:39.046
but I actually really look up to you and...

28:39.120 --> 28:41.361
- You said Beth's alive.
- Yeah!

28:41.440 --> 28:44.922
Yeah, she is, and it's so great.
It's like love conquers all.

28:45.000 --> 28:47.720
- You're making fun of me or something?
- No, it's totally the truth.

28:47.760 --> 28:49.683
- Close the door, Zach.
- Just open your heart.

28:49.760 --> 28:52.047
- Close the door, psycho!
- Okay.

28:52.960 --> 28:55.361
(INDISTINCT CHATTER OVER RADIO)

28:55.640 --> 28:57.642
- No, get the fuck out of my room!
- Okay!

28:57.720 --> 29:00.564
- Close the door on your way out!
- Okay!

29:02.520 --> 29:03.521
Good morning.

29:06.360 --> 29:07.920
JUDY: Look who's got his appetite back.

29:07.960 --> 29:09.450
All that pool watching.

29:09.560 --> 29:10.971
You're up pretty early, son.

29:11.040 --> 29:12.963
Or is it really, really late?

29:13.040 --> 29:15.725
I mean, it's all relative, you know?
(LAUGHS)

29:15.800 --> 29:16.801
Not really, no.

29:16.880 --> 29:20.851
Well, it's like there's no past, no future,
no up or down.

29:20.920 --> 29:23.810
No dead or alive.

29:23.880 --> 29:25.484
Jesus realized this.

29:28.120 --> 29:29.121
(CAR DOOR SHUTS)

29:29.200 --> 29:30.725
CHIP: Zachster.

29:30.960 --> 29:32.530
ZACH: Whoa! Chip? (LAUGHING)

29:32.840 --> 29:35.684
Whoa! Where have you been?
What happened to you?

29:35.760 --> 29:37.091
Well, nothing. What do you mean?

29:37.160 --> 29:40.846
I haven't seen you since before college.

29:40.920 --> 29:42.570
Oh. You seem like you're kind of down, kid.

29:42.640 --> 29:44.608
No, I'm totally good.

29:47.160 --> 29:48.161
Um...

29:48.320 --> 29:49.924
This isn't our mail.

29:50.000 --> 29:52.970
Okay, well, we'll catch you tomorrow.

29:53.160 --> 29:54.161
What?

29:56.440 --> 29:57.441
(ENGINE STARTING)

30:15.120 --> 30:17.600
GEENIE: I know it's a
frustrating situation.

30:17.680 --> 30:19.921
Yeah, I understand.

30:20.400 --> 30:21.447
Uh-huh.

30:21.520 --> 30:23.090
Why don't you tell them to tell...

30:23.160 --> 30:24.366
MAURY: Unbelievable.

30:25.360 --> 30:27.089
She's building something.

30:27.160 --> 30:31.802
You know,
we really should let Beth know she died.

30:31.880 --> 30:35.566
- No. No.
- Well, I've opened up to her, you know?

30:35.640 --> 30:40.123
Yeah, but no, we're not gonna do that.
That'll just confuse her and make her upset.

30:40.200 --> 30:42.123
- That's not happening.
- GEENIE: Honey?

30:42.200 --> 30:43.361
What should I tell them?

30:43.440 --> 30:46.011
Tell them I'll come back
when I'm ready to come back.

30:46.080 --> 30:48.242
They have to stop calling
every five minutes.

30:48.320 --> 30:50.368
- Look, she came back, right?
- Right.

30:50.440 --> 30:52.522
- And that is for a reason.
- Well...

30:52.600 --> 30:55.922
Also I think Pearline might have
something to do with this.

30:56.040 --> 30:57.530
- 'Cause she...
- No. Yeah, no.

30:57.600 --> 30:59.967
She disappeared
right before Beth appeared.

31:00.040 --> 31:01.166
- And she's Haitian.
- No.

31:01.240 --> 31:03.242
- Just think about it like this...
- Zachy. Zachy.

31:03.320 --> 31:05.846
You're going down a rabbit hole.
This doesn't make any sense.

31:05.920 --> 31:08.651
And I need you to tell me
that you won't tell her.

31:08.760 --> 31:11.127
Look, I understand how scared you are.

31:11.200 --> 31:14.044
Listen, she's my daughter.
I make the rules.

31:14.120 --> 31:16.521
And if you want to be in my house,

31:16.600 --> 31:19.206
you will promise me
that you are not gonna tell her.

31:24.680 --> 31:25.920
Okay.

31:26.760 --> 31:28.125
I promise.

31:29.920 --> 31:31.763
MAURY: There she is!
ZACH: Hey.

31:32.280 --> 31:33.964
Beth, oh, I missed you so much.

31:34.040 --> 31:35.849
I missed you more.

31:37.120 --> 31:38.121
(BOTH MOANING)

31:38.200 --> 31:40.441
All right, that's enough of that!

31:40.520 --> 31:41.931
Zach and I are going on a hike.

31:42.000 --> 31:45.288
What? Uh-uh. No. No way!

31:45.360 --> 31:48.523
I think that is important that we do this.

31:48.600 --> 31:50.284
No. Beth? Bethy?

31:50.920 --> 31:51.920
Bethy?

31:51.960 --> 31:53.405
You are not to leave this house.

31:53.480 --> 31:55.528
- Not in the daylight.
- BETH: Not in the daylight?

31:55.640 --> 31:58.246
- Why are you acting like I'm a child?
- Yeah, tell her, Maury.

31:58.320 --> 32:01.324
"Maury"? Since when did you
start calling my dad Maury? Ew!

32:02.280 --> 32:04.044
Zach, this really isn't a good idea.

32:04.120 --> 32:05.565
- No, it's fine.
- Zach.

32:05.640 --> 32:07.130
It's really...

32:07.200 --> 32:09.646
Zach, please don't do this.

32:09.720 --> 32:12.724
Maury, it's cool. Trust me.

32:16.480 --> 32:18.084
Okay!

32:18.160 --> 32:20.322
Well, have fun.
When can I expect you back?

32:20.400 --> 32:21.765
Dad, stop!

32:22.680 --> 32:24.011
Bye, Maury.

32:57.920 --> 32:58.921
(BOTH PANTING)

33:10.200 --> 33:13.921
It's crazy, you know?
Like it all makes sense.

33:14.000 --> 33:19.131
It's like there's no inside without outside
or light without dark.

33:19.200 --> 33:20.770
They're the same.

33:22.360 --> 33:24.522
I mean, I want to say that I understand it,

33:24.600 --> 33:28.207
- but it's like I don't which means I do.
- Huh.

33:30.200 --> 33:33.044
You're so expressive now. It's cute.

33:35.680 --> 33:38.206
Ah. Her face has a huge blister.

33:38.280 --> 33:39.645
It's not a blister. It's sunburn.

33:39.720 --> 33:41.609
I just got a little color. That's all.

33:41.680 --> 33:42.761
It's charred.

33:42.840 --> 33:44.729
- Look at it.
- Looks cute. (GRUNTS)

33:45.840 --> 33:48.525
Okay, Zach. Zach! You're acting manic.

33:48.600 --> 33:49.931
It doesn't hurt. I'm fine.

33:50.000 --> 33:51.001
Okay, no more.

33:51.080 --> 33:52.889
- Honey, relax.
- You see, I told you shouldn't go,

33:52.960 --> 33:55.406
and now look. Look what happens.

33:55.480 --> 33:58.211
Honey, we'll just put
a little foundation on it.

33:58.280 --> 34:00.487
Mom, it's just a sunburn.
It's not that big of a deal.

34:00.600 --> 34:01.601
That's right.

34:01.680 --> 34:04.081
Maybe you should put some aloe on it
or something and a Band-Aid.

34:04.160 --> 34:06.322
Aloe? You think aloe's gonna do anything?

34:06.440 --> 34:08.090
- No more outings.
- ZACH: Whoa, whoa! Maury?

34:08.159 --> 34:10.731
Don't you go over my head, Zach.
That's final!

34:10.800 --> 34:12.404
Or we can use some of the aloe
from our front lawn.

34:12.480 --> 34:14.130
Geenie, stop triangulating.

34:14.199 --> 34:17.283
You know what? Maybe if we were just all
completely honest with one another...

34:17.360 --> 34:19.089
Enough already. Will you stop?

34:19.199 --> 34:22.170
No, you know what? Maury you are just
too jazzed to know what's what.

34:22.239 --> 34:24.766
Okay, look, this is simple.
If we just tell her...

34:24.840 --> 34:28.049
No. "Jazzed"? You want to know jazzed?
I'll tell you what, pal.

34:28.120 --> 34:31.442
I know! I know! I know!

34:31.520 --> 34:34.444
I have to study for my test. Jeez.

34:35.560 --> 34:38.245
- Right. That's right, Beth.
- Yeah, that is a good idea.

34:38.320 --> 34:39.844
You have to study for your test.

34:39.920 --> 34:42.206
Yeah, I should probably go,
so she can study for her test.

34:42.280 --> 34:45.329
Yeah, you better go.
'Cause Beth has to study for her test.

34:45.400 --> 34:47.801
GEENIE: Yeah. We'll get some studying...

34:53.159 --> 34:54.161
(BETH MOANING)

34:55.360 --> 34:56.646
Okay!

34:57.640 --> 34:59.927
That's enough of that now, kids, come on.

35:00.000 --> 35:02.162
It's not fun. It's weird.

35:02.240 --> 35:05.164
End of kiss, guys. Okay.
Let's hit those books.

35:06.160 --> 35:08.481
- I love you.
- I love you, too.

35:16.920 --> 35:18.843
We have to be on the same team.

35:18.920 --> 35:21.002
What? I was backing you up.

35:24.040 --> 35:26.327
